{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958607,"nonce":"md4Txf0FA4+NII2YNHqBQmLWaT8=","kind":"plans","title":"TTY-aware full help (`--full` / `--short`) Implementation Plan","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958607,"nonce":"O9JlQVLWTpgldzHvYId1XLNEabk=","body":"# TTY-aware full help (`--full` / `--short`) Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Make `kref` help adapt to its output writer — concise on a terminal, a full recursive tree (every command, flag, example, plus a global output-contract preamble) when piped to an agent — with explicit `--full` / `--short` overrides on a custom `help` command.\n\n**Architecture:** A single `renderHelp(cmd, mode, defaultHelp)` dispatcher funnels both the `-h`/`--help` flag path (via `SetHelpFunc`) and a custom `help` command. Mode `auto` resolves off `cmd.OutOrStdout()` type-asserted to `*os.File` (full only for a real non-terminal file; buffers/terminals → concise, keeping tests deterministic). The concise branch delegates to cobra's captured stock help func (preserving the existing alias/group template). The full branch hand-walks the command subtree as plain text.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, `github.com/spf13/cobra` v1.10.2, `golang.org/x/term`, Ginkgo/Gomega tests run via `task test`.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-30-tty-aware-full-help-design.md`\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Create `cmd/kref/help.go`** — all help rendering: `helpMode` enum, `fullByDefault`, `renderHelp`, `renderFull`, preamble/grouped/per-command writers, `indentBlock`, `commandHeading`, `newHelpCmd`, `helpTargetCompletions`. One responsibility: turning the command tree into help text. Keeps `main.go` (wiring) and `output.go` (result emission) untouched in responsibility.\n- **Modify `cmd/kref/main.go`** — in `newRootCmd`, replace the `SetHelpCommandGroupID` line with: capture `defaultHelp`, `SetHelpFunc`, and `SetHelpCommand(newHelpCmd(...))`. Add `\"errors\"` import only if not already present (it is not — main.go currently imports `encoding/json`, `fmt`, `os`, `strings`, `cobra`; `errors` is used only inside help.go, so main.go imports are unchanged).\n- **Modify `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`** — add Describe blocks for full/short/scoping/error/drift, plus unit specs for `fullByDefault` and `helpTargetCompletions`.\n- **Modify `README.md`** — document `kref help --full` / `--short` and the auto behavior under the existing \"Command reference\" section.\n\n`aliasedName(c)` already exists in `main.go:87` and is reused by `commandHeading` — do not redefine it.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Help rendering core (`help.go`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `cmd/kref/help.go`\n- Test: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (append new specs)\n\nThis task adds the rendering functions and tests them directly against the\nalready-built `newRootCmd()` tree. `main.go` is NOT wired yet, so all existing\ntests must keep passing.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"fullByDefault\", func() {\n\tIt(\"is false for a non-file writer such as a test buffer\", func() {\n\t\tExpect(fullByDefault(\u0026bytes.Buffer{})).To(BeFalse())\n\t})\n\tIt(\"is true for a non-terminal file (a pipe)\", func() {\n\t\tr, w, err := os.Pipe()\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tdefer r.Close()\n\t\tdefer w.Close()\n\t\tExpect(fullByDefault(w)).To(BeTrue())\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"renderFull\", func() {\n\tIt(\"emits the global preamble and recurses into second-level commands\", func() {\n\t\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\t\troot := newRootCmd()\n\t\trenderFull(\u0026buf, root)\n\t\tout := buf.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"GLOBAL FLAGS\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"OUTPUT CONTRACT\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--json\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--dir\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--actor\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Core Commands:\"))\n\t\t// \"backup\" is a child of \"vault\" — only the recursive walk reaches it.\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"backup\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"scopes to the named command's subtree, omitting group headers\", func() {\n\t\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\t\troot := newRootCmd()\n\t\tsync, _, err := root.Find([]string{\"sync\"})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\trenderFull(\u0026buf, sync)\n\t\tout := buf.String()\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"push\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"pull\"))\n\t\t// group titles are emitted only for the root walk:\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Sync Commands:\"))\n\t})\n})\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"helpTargetCompletions\", func() {\n\tIt(\"completes top-level command names with no args\", func() {\n\t\tnames, _ := helpTargetCompletions(newRootCmd(), nil, \"\")\n\t\tExpect(names).To(ContainElement(\"add\"))\n\t\tExpect(names).To(ContainElement(\"sync\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"completes a parent's subcommands\", func() {\n\t\tnames, _ := helpTargetCompletions(newRootCmd(), []string{\"sync\"}, \"\")\n\t\tExpect(names).To(ContainElement(\"push\"))\n\t\tExpect(names).To(ContainElement(\"pull\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `go test ./cmd/kref/ -run TestKref 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: compile failure — `undefined: fullByDefault`, `undefined: renderFull`, `undefined: helpTargetCompletions`.\n\n(The Ginkgo suite entry point is a single `TestKref`-style function; if the\nexact name differs, run `go test ./cmd/kref/` — the failure is a compile error\neither way.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Create `cmd/kref/help.go`**\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n\t\"golang.org/x/term\"\n)\n\n// helpMode selects how renderHelp renders. helpAuto resolves by the command's\n// output writer; helpFull and helpShort are the explicit --full / --short\n// overrides carried by the help command.\ntype helpMode int\n\nconst (\n\thelpAuto helpMode = iota\n\thelpFull\n\thelpShort\n)\n\n// fullByDefault reports whether help written to w should render the full\n// recursive tree. It keys off the command's own writer rather than os.Stdout so\n// the Ginkgo specs — which capture output into a *bytes.Buffer via cmd.SetOut —\n// are deterministic: only a real file whose fd is not a terminal (a pipe or\n// redirect, e.g. an agent capturing stdout) yields full. A terminal, or any\n// non-file writer such as a test buffer, yields concise.\nfunc fullByDefault(w io.Writer) bool {\n\tf, ok := w.(*os.File)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\treturn !term.IsTerminal(int(f.Fd()))\n}\n\n// renderHelp is the single path both the -h/--help flag (via SetHelpFunc) and\n// the custom help command funnel through. defaultHelp is cobra's stock help\n// renderer, captured before SetHelpFunc replaces it, so the concise branch\n// reproduces today's grouped/aliased output exactly.\nfunc renderHelp(cmd *cobra.Command, mode helpMode, defaultHelp func(*cobra.Command, []string)) {\n\tfull := mode == helpFull || (mode == helpAuto \u0026\u0026 fullByDefault(cmd.OutOrStdout()))\n\tif !full {\n\t\tdefaultHelp(cmd, nil)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\trenderFull(cmd.OutOrStdout(), cmd)\n}\n\n// renderFull writes the agent-oriented expanded help for target and everything\n// under it. For the root it lists commands under their group titles; for a\n// subcommand it expands that command's own subtree. The global preamble is\n// always shown because the persistent flags and output contract apply tree-wide.\nfunc renderFull(w io.Writer, target *cobra.Command) {\n\troot := target.Root()\n\twriteHelpPreamble(w, root)\n\tif target == root {\n\t\twriteGroupedCommands(w, root)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\twriteCommandFull(w, target, 0)\n}\n\n// writeHelpPreamble renders the cross-cutting facts an agent cannot infer per\n// command: the global persistent flags (rendered from the live flag set, so\n// they cannot drift) and the JSON output / exit-code contract.\nfunc writeHelpPreamble(w io.Writer, root *cobra.Command) {\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s — %s\\n\\n\", root.Name(), root.Short)\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"GLOBAL FLAGS\")\n\tfmt.Fprint(w, root.PersistentFlags().FlagUsages())\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w)\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"OUTPUT CONTRACT\")\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"  Human-readable text by default; pass --json for machine-readable objects.\")\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"  Under --json, errors are emitted as a single line: {\\\"error\\\": \\\"\u003cmessage\u003e\\\"}.\")\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w, \"  Exit status is 0 on success and 1 on any error.\")\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w)\n}\n\n// writeGroupedCommands lists the root's commands under their group titles, in\n// registration order (cobra.EnableCommandSorting is false), recursing into each.\nfunc writeGroupedCommands(w io.Writer, root *cobra.Command) {\n\tfor _, g := range root.Groups() {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s\\n\", g.Title)\n\t\tfor _, c := range root.Commands() {\n\t\t\tif c.GroupID != g.ID || !c.IsAvailableCommand() {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\twriteCommandFull(w, c, 1)\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w)\n\t}\n}\n\n// writeCommandFull renders one command — heading, long description, local\n// flags, examples — at the given indent depth, then recurses into its available\n// subcommands.\nfunc writeCommandFull(w io.Writer, c *cobra.Command, depth int) {\n\tind := strings.Repeat(\"  \", depth)\n\tbody := ind + \"  \"\n\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s%s\\n\", ind, commandHeading(c))\n\tif c.Long != \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(w, indentBlock(c.Long, body))\n\t}\n\tif usage := strings.TrimRight(c.LocalFlags().FlagUsages(), \"\\n\"); strings.TrimSpace(usage) != \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%sFlags:\\n\", body)\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(w, indentBlock(usage, body+\"  \"))\n\t}\n\tif c.Example != \"\" {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"%sExamples:\\n\", body)\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(w, indentBlock(c.Example, body+\"  \"))\n\t}\n\tfmt.Fprintln(w)\n\tfor _, sub := range c.Commands() {\n\t\tif sub.IsAvailableCommand() {\n\t\t\twriteCommandFull(w, sub, depth+1)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// commandHeading renders a command's heading line: \"name (alias, …)  —  Short\".\nfunc commandHeading(c *cobra.Command) string {\n\tname := aliasedName(c)\n\tif c.Short == \"\" {\n\t\treturn name\n\t}\n\treturn name + \"  —  \" + c.Short\n}\n\n// indentBlock prefixes every non-empty line of s with indent and guarantees a\n// trailing newline.\nfunc indentBlock(s, indent string) string {\n\tlines := strings.Split(strings.TrimRight(s, \"\\n\"), \"\\n\")\n\tfor i, ln := range lines {\n\t\tif ln != \"\" {\n\t\t\tlines[i] = indent + ln\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn strings.Join(lines, \"\\n\") + \"\\n\"\n}\n\n// newHelpCmd builds a custom replacement for cobra's auto-generated help\n// command, adding --full / --short overrides while preserving the \"additional\"\n// group placement and subcommand-name completion.\nfunc newHelpCmd(root *cobra.Command, defaultHelp func(*cobra.Command, []string)) *cobra.Command {\n\tvar full, short bool\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:     \"help [command]\",\n\t\tShort:   \"Help about any command\",\n\t\tGroupID: \"additional\",\n\t\tLong: \"Help prints usage for kref or a specific command.\\n\\n\" +\n\t\t\t\"Depth adapts to the output: a terminal gets the concise grouped command \" +\n\t\t\t\"list, while a pipe or redirect (what an agent sees) gets the full recursive \" +\n\t\t\t\"tree with every command, flag, example, and the global output contract. \" +\n\t\t\t\"Force either depth with --full or --short.\",\n\t\tValidArgsFunction: func(c *cobra.Command, args []string, toComplete string) ([]string, cobra.ShellCompDirective) {\n\t\t\treturn helpTargetCompletions(c.Root(), args, toComplete)\n\t\t},\n\t\tRunE: func(c *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\tif full \u0026\u0026 short {\n\t\t\t\treturn errors.New(\"--full and --short cannot be combined\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\ttarget, _, err := c.Root().Find(args)\n\t\t\tif err != nil || target == nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unknown help topic %q\", strings.Join(args, \" \"))\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tmode := helpAuto\n\t\t\tswitch {\n\t\t\tcase full:\n\t\t\t\tmode = helpFull\n\t\t\tcase short:\n\t\t\t\tmode = helpShort\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\trenderHelp(target, mode, defaultHelp)\n\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tc.Flags().BoolVar(\u0026full, \"full\", false, \"show the full recursive command tree, flags, and examples\")\n\tc.Flags().BoolVar(\u0026short, \"short\", false, \"show the concise grouped command list\")\n\treturn c\n}\n\n// helpTargetCompletions completes the command-name argument to `kref help`,\n// offering the available subcommands of whatever parent the prior args resolve\n// to (the root when there are none). Preserves `kref help \u003cTAB\u003e`.\nfunc helpTargetCompletions(root *cobra.Command, args []string, _ string) ([]string, cobra.ShellCompDirective) {\n\ttarget, _, err := root.Find(args)\n\tif err != nil || target == nil {\n\t\ttarget = root\n\t}\n\tvar names []string\n\tfor _, c := range target.Commands() {\n\t\tif c.IsAvailableCommand() {\n\t\t\tnames = append(names, c.Name())\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn names, cobra.ShellCompDirectiveNoFileComp\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -20`\nExpected: PASS (all specs, including the pre-existing ones, green).\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/help.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(help): add full recursive help renderer and helpers\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Wire help into the root command (`main.go`)\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go:79` (the `SetHelpCommandGroupID` line and surrounding return)\n- Test: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (append integration specs)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing integration tests**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"kref help --full / --short\", func() {\n\tIt(\"expands the whole tree with the output contract under --full\", func() {\n\t\tout := run(\"help\", \"--full\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"OUTPUT CONTRACT\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--json\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"backup\")) // second-level command\n\t})\n\tIt(\"scopes --full to the named command's subtree\", func() {\n\t\tout := run(\"help\", \"sync\", \"--full\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"push\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"pull\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Sync Commands:\")) // no group headers off-root\n\t})\n\tIt(\"forces the concise grouped list under --short\", func() {\n\t\tout := run(\"help\", \"--short\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Core Commands:\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"OUTPUT CONTRACT\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"backup\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"defaults to concise for a buffer writer (deterministic in tests)\", func() {\n\t\tout := run(\"--help\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"Core Commands:\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"OUTPUT CONTRACT\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"rejects --full and --short together\", func() {\n\t\tvar buf bytes.Buffer\n\t\tc := newRootCmd()\n\t\tc.SetOut(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetErr(\u0026buf)\n\t\tc.SetArgs([]string{\"help\", \"--full\", \"--short\"})\n\t\terr := c.Execute()\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(err.Error()).To(ContainSubstring(\"cannot be combined\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `go test ./cmd/kref/ -run TestKref 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -25`\nExpected: the four `run(\"help\", …)` / `run(\"--help\")` specs FAIL — without wiring, `help --full` is an unknown flag (cobra's stock help command has no `--full`), so `run` errors or the output lacks \"OUTPUT CONTRACT\".\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Wire the renderer into `newRootCmd`**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, replace this block (currently around lines 79–82):\n\n```go\n\troot.SetHelpCommandGroupID(\"additional\")\n\n\tlistAliasesInUsage(root)\n\treturn root\n}\n```\n\nwith:\n\n```go\n\tlistAliasesInUsage(root)\n\n\t// Capture cobra's stock help renderer BEFORE overriding it, so the concise\n\t// branch of renderHelp reproduces today's grouped/aliased output exactly.\n\tdefaultHelp := root.HelpFunc()\n\troot.SetHelpFunc(func(c *cobra.Command, _ []string) {\n\t\trenderHelp(c, helpAuto, defaultHelp)\n\t})\n\troot.SetHelpCommand(newHelpCmd(root, defaultHelp))\n\treturn root\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -25`\nExpected: PASS — new help specs green AND the pre-existing `help grouping`,\n`command aliases`, and `lists aliases inline in the top-level --help` specs\nstill green (concise path unchanged via the captured default).\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Build and eyeball the real binary (interactive vs piped)**\n\nRun:\n```bash\ntask build \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref --help | head -5 \u0026\u0026 echo \"--- piped (full) ---\" \u0026\u0026 ./bin/kref --help | grep -c \"OUTPUT CONTRACT\"\n```\nExpected: the first `--help` is captured by the pipe → full, so `OUTPUT CONTRACT` count is `1`. (Running `./bin/kref --help` directly in your terminal shows the concise grouped list.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(help): render full help on non-terminal stdout, add --full/--short\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Drift guard + documentation\n\n**Files:**\n- Test: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (append drift-guard spec)\n- Modify: `README.md` (under \"## Command reference\", around line 575)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing drift-guard test**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"help preamble drift guard\", func() {\n\tIt(\"names only global flags that actually exist on the root\", func() {\n\t\troot := newRootCmd()\n\t\tfor _, name := range []string{\"json\", \"dir\", \"actor\"} {\n\t\t\tExpect(root.PersistentFlags().Lookup(name)).NotTo(BeNil(),\n\t\t\t\t\"global flag --%s referenced by the help preamble must exist\", name)\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\tIt(\"renders every global flag in the full preamble\", func() {\n\t\tout := run(\"help\", \"--full\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--json\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--dir\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--actor\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run to verify it passes immediately**\n\nRun: `go test ./cmd/kref/ -run TestKref 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -10`\nExpected: PASS. The preamble renders flags from the live flag set (Task 1), so\nthis guard already holds — it exists to FAIL loudly if a future change renames\nor drops a global flag while the preamble prose still references it.\n\n(This is the rare case where the test is green on first write: it guards an\ninvariant the implementation already satisfies. No production change accompanies\nit.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Document in README**\n\nIn `README.md`, under the `## Command reference` section (around line 575), add this subsection immediately after the section heading's intro:\n\n```markdown\n### Help depth\n\n`kref help` and `kref --help` adapt to where output goes. On an interactive\nterminal you get the concise, grouped command list. When stdout is a pipe or\nredirect — which is what an automated agent sees — `kref` prints the **full**\nrecursive tree instead: every command and subcommand, their flags and examples,\nplus a preamble covering the global flags (`--json`, `--dir`, `--actor`) and the\nJSON output / exit-code contract.\n\nForce either depth explicitly on the `help` command:\n\n```\nkref help --full      # full tree, regardless of terminal\nkref help --short      # concise list, regardless of pipe\nkref help sync --full  # full help scoped to one command's subtree\n```\n\n`--full` and `--short` cannot be combined.\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the full gate**\n\nRun: `task test`\nExpected: PASS. (Run via `task test`, not bare `go test ./...`: it wires\n`KREF_GITLEAKS` for the scan specs and exercises cross-package suites. The help\nfeature itself touches no scan path, but the project gate is `task test`.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/cli_test.go README.md\ngit commit -m \"feat(help): guard preamble against flag drift, document help depth\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Self-Review Notes\n\n- **Spec coverage:**\n  - Behavior table (auto/full/short × terminal/pipe) → Task 2 specs + Task 1 `fullByDefault`.\n  - `cmd.OutOrStdout()` detection → `fullByDefault` (Task 1).\n  - Two entry points (flag path TTY-auto; help command carries flags) → Task 2 wiring (`SetHelpFunc` + `newHelpCmd`).\n  - Mutual exclusion → Task 2 error spec.\n  - Recursive \"from invoked command down\" → `renderFull` root vs subcommand branches (Task 1).\n  - Plain-text approach A (no cobra/doc) → `writeCommandFull` (Task 1).\n  - Agent preamble (globals from live flags + output contract) → `writeHelpPreamble` (Task 1).\n  - Drift guard → Task 3.\n  - Preserve alias/group concise output → concise branch delegates to captured `defaultHelp`; verified by unchanged pre-existing specs (Task 2 Step 4).\n  - Preserve `kref help \u003cTAB\u003e` completion → `helpTargetCompletions` (Task 1) + `ValidArgsFunction` wiring (Task 2).\n  - Preserve `additional` group placement → `GroupID: \"additional\"` on the custom help command (Task 1), replacing `SetHelpCommandGroupID`.\n  - Docs → Task 3 README.\n- **Placeholder scan:** none — every step has runnable code/commands.\n- **Type consistency:** `helpMode`/`helpAuto`/`helpFull`/`helpShort`, `renderHelp(cmd, mode, defaultHelp)`, `renderFull(w, target)`, `fullByDefault(w)`, `helpTargetCompletions(root, args, _)`, `newHelpCmd(root, defaultHelp)` used identically across tasks. `aliasedName` is the existing `main.go` helper, reused not redefined."}]}